    <!-- Application Structure Plan: 
         Designed as a "Digital Research Dashboard" to allow non-linear exploration.
         1. Header: Immersive branding and context.
         2. Navigation Bar: Sticky tabs for 3 core pillars (Culture, Data, Modernization).
         3. Dynamic Viewport:
            - View A (Culture): Split screen list/detail view for Ghats using interaction to reveal history.
            - View B (Data): Dashboard grid with Chart.js to visualize tourism and demographics.
            - View C (Modernization): Comparative layout showing infrastructure upgrades.
         Rationale: Users can switch between qualitative stories and quantitative hard data easily without losing context.
    -->

    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices:
         1. Tourism Growth (Line Chart): To show the massive spike post-Corridor project. Goal: Compare trends over time.
         2. Visitor Demographics (Doughnut): To breakdown domestic vs international interest. Goal: Inform composition.
         3. Seasonal Flux (Bar Chart): To show best times to visit. Goal: Planning/Analysis.
         4. Ghats Interactive List: Text-based interaction. Goal: Organize complex cultural points into digestible bites.
         All implemented via Chart.js and vanilla JS DOM manipulation.
    -->

    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
